title: The Vamps release Wake Up single
text:
The Vamps release Wake Up single The Vamps release Wake Up single Share 
The Vamps have unveiled their new single, Wake Up, to the excitement of their fans. 
The boyband – Connor Ball, Tristan Evans, James Daniel McVey and Brad Simpson – released the track, along with a teaser clip of the video. Wake Up is OUT NOW!!! Get it from our store http://t.co/6ebbTwTWJQ or iTunes: http://t.co/fKOLnoAlUS https://t.co/lm24XscdDx 
— The Vamps (@TheVampsband) October 2, 2015 
The song, which premiered just hours ago, is riding high in the iTunes chart and is already in the top 20 of the singles section. 
The full video, which will feature their friend Brooklyn Beckham, will premiere on YouTube on October 5. 
— Brooklyn Beckham (@brooklynbeckham) August 9, 2015 
The group said: “Making the music video for Wake Up was something we were super excited about! It has been a year since we did our last shoot, and we were eager to get involved in a new one. 
“This video was something we had never done before; we performed on top of a radio tower, 100 feet in the air. It was pretty scary, but absolutely awesome.” The Vamps (Lindsey Byrnes/VirginEMI) 
They added: “We were lucky enough to have Brooklyn Beckham in the video, he’s a super nice guy and crazy talented.” Share article 
Wake Up is the lead single from The Vamps’ new album, which follows on November 27. Promoted Stories
